    "comment": "Rationale: The authors use a PKA RII beta knockout mouse to study its role in synaptic plasticity in the visual cortex. It is shown that long term depression (LTD) is abolished in layer V of the visual cortex.\n\nLTD is a postsynaptic process that requires the endocytosis of AMPA receptors (Beattie et al.,Kirkwood and Bear). In the hippocampus, PKA-mediated phosphorylation of GluR1 is required for AMPA trafficking. It has not formally been shown if this is also true in LTD in the visual cortex.. Experimental description: Generation of knock-out and wild-type mice The initial generation of RIIb-/- and AC1/AC8-/-\nmice has been described previously (Brandon et al., 1998; Wong et al., 1999). Here, to\ncontrol for modifiers, mutants were subsequently back-crossed seven or\nmore times into either 129 (129S1/SvImJ; Jackson Laboratories, Bar Har-\nbor, ME) or B6 (C57BL/6; Taconic Farms Inc., Germantown, NY) lines\nfor study.",
